UPDATE: The electricity has been restored and it seems that the transistor has been fixed. No other outages are expected.  Also read: BREAKING NEWS: Pedestrian killed on the N4 last night  MBOMBELA – Most of the city was without electricity this morning. Mbombela fire department says that they are working on a transformer at Laerskool Laeveld that is giving problems. They also said that the power should be on in one to two hours. This transformer also supplies power to I’langa Mall. Lowvelder will keep you posted as soon as more information becomes available.